This is not a link; it is just text (although your browser may be interpreting it and rendering it as a clickable link).  

The `A` tag is used to identify links; it has an `href` attribute which is the URL to link to, and the text between `&lt;A&gt;` and `&lt;/A&gt;` can be anything you want.  SO, for your example, you would use:

    &lt;A href=&quot;http://55.55.555.555&quot;&gt;www.anyurl.com&lt;/A&gt;

You can provide any value in between the &lt;a&gt; tags and that value will come as the name of the link.

    &lt;a href=&quot;http://55.55.555.555&quot;&gt;www.anyurl.com&lt;/a&gt;

&lt;td&gt; is a table data element. Writing a url within &lt;td&gt; elements will not make it a link. To create a link you have to use &lt;a&gt; tag

